cs.DC, cs.DB, cs.CE, cs.CR, cs.SE 

This paper discusses the challenges and approaches for processing large amounts of data, which is a common topic in the areas of distributed computing (cs.DC), databases (cs.DB), computational engineering (cs.CE), computer security and cryptography (cs.CR), and software engineering (cs.SE). The paper specifically focuses on the comparison of two prominent paradigms for data-intensive applications, which is relevant to all of these sub-categories. However, given the emphasis on distributed computing and data management, cs.DC and cs.DB are the most likely sub-categories.
